This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing and dialogue systems, which suggests that it would likely fall under the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning models, specifically encoder-decoder models, which would also fit under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also discusses the development of representations by the model, which could fall under the cs.LG (Learning) category. The use of visualisation and diagnostic classifiers suggests a focus on interpretability, which could fall under the cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing, Speech and Audio Processing) category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact on task success, which could fall under the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) category.
